# .leakignore — allowlist for check-no-private-leaks.sh
#
# Format per line: <path-glob> <tag[,tag...]>  # reason
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are skipped.
#
# A violation is suppressed only if BOTH the path matches the glob AND
# the emitted tag is listed.
#
# Keep entries to path-globs + tags only — the scanner reads this file
# too, so paths/credentials in a comment or entry are not suppressed.
#
# .vercel/project.json is gitignored (.gitignore:34) and never committed.
# The scanner flags it from the on-disk working-tree file. Suppressed here
# because the public repo never contains these IDs; re-verify with
# `git ls-files .vercel/` before any public flip (must return empty).
.vercel/project.json vercel-org-id,vercel-project-id
